title: Former Medicare chief to head health insurance lobby AHIP
text: RSS Politico , July 16, 2015 Former Medicare chief Marilyn Tavenner has been hired as the new CEO of America's Health Insurance Plans, representing an industry that she helped regulate during the turbulent launch of Obamacare. The powerful K Street lobbying group's announcement Wednesday comes months after Tavenner, a nurse and former hospital CEO, stepped down as the administrator of the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services. At the agency, she was responsible for writing many of Obamacare's rules and oversaw the troubled rollout ? and repair ? of the HealthCare.gov enrollment website.
